{
  "stem": "443.1",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I've worked with Germans, and I've worked with Poles, and I've worked with people from all over the world.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were in civil clothes, but they came to work every day in the factories.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "While we were in this camp, it was clean.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were 200 in a barrack.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we got, every morning, something to eat before we went to work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But it was very cold.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was winter time.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And to survive-- the only way we survive, we slept five together in one cot to keep each warm.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's funny, we were talking about it when I was in-- in-- in-- in Washington.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I looked at the cots.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I said to my daughter, you see, I slept first in the middle, then I slept on the outside, then I slept the second one, because kept on changing each other so you should keep each the warm in the winter nights.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It's just the unbelievable where a person-- how a person can survive.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] After about six months, they start to bomb the camp because there was a lot of factories.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were trying to get to the factories.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "During the day, we used to see the Russians.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because we could see the stars with the Russian writing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They came so low that we could see the Russian planes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "At night, used to come either the English or the Americans, because they used to lit up to the skies.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was so bright during the night when they came to bomb, they used to lit up the whole sky.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So you could see the Americans, the English.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when they start to bomb, we obviously used to run out of the barracks, used to lay in the fields.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
